The following files in the Nova source tree are ports of (and in places
near-verbatim adaptations of) algorithms from the Go programming language
runtime (https://github.com/golang/go, tag go1.4, src/runtime/), used under
the BSD-3-Clause license reproduced below:

  - compiler-codegen/nova_rt/runq.h        (proc.c: runqput/runqputslow/
                                            runqget/runqgrab/runqsteal,
                                            globrunqputbatch/globrunqget)
  - (further files added as Plan 83-study-go-c-mn phases land — see that plan)

Type names and primitives are adapted to Nova (G* -> mco_coro*,
runtime·cas/atomicload/atomicstore -> C11 __atomic builtins, the global
sched.lock -> a Nova spinlock); the algorithm, control flow, variable names,
and inline comments are preserved from the Go original. Each ported function
carries an in-file reference to its go1.4 origin.

